# SumelaOS — second-brain ledger merge strategy.
#
# _LOG.md is an append-only chronological ledger (entries: `## [YYYY-MM-DD] type | topic`).
# Git's built-in `union` merge driver concatenates BOTH sides of a conflicting
# append instead of raising a merge conflict, so log entries written concurrently
# on different branches/by different developers combine cleanly on merge.
#
# This is safe ONLY for append-only files. Do not apply `union` to structured
# files (active-project-context.md, _SEARCH_INDEX.md) — there it would duplicate
# or garble sections. The improvement queue avoids conflicts via per-entry files
# (one file per signal), not a merge driver.
#
# Caveats:
#  - Rotation/`migration` (moving old entries to wiki/archive/_LOG-YYYY.md) REWRITES
#    _LOG.md and temporarily violates append-only. Do rotation on the integration
#    branch (or merge it before others diverge) — union would silently mis-merge a
#    rotation against concurrent edits instead of raising a reviewable conflict.
#  - This rule is hardcoded to the default wiki path. If you relocate the wiki
#    (custom WIKI_PATH), update this path or union protection silently won't apply.
docs/second-brain/wiki/_LOG.md merge=union

# The managed-.gitignore single source is matched line-for-line by setup/update on
# both shells — pin it to LF so a Windows checkout can't introduce CRLF mismatches.
scripts/lib/sumela-gitignore.list text eol=lf
